rComments: Professor Backhouse's thematic class on legal history made my 1L year. Yes as others have said she had strong political views but she's very open to hearing from and learning from students. She is so caring and one of the only profs I truly believe when she says she wants us to succeed.
Respected scholar in this area, highly knowledgeable. Strong views, and pushes students to develop strong views in this area.

What is everyone's problem?? Can't you read a course discription??  If you are a right-winger and you don't want to hear people from the left, don't take their class! There are tonnes of "black-letter" crim classes that have no social perspective whatsoever.  Don't blame the prof because you can't read a course discription!
If you're a lefty, then her classes will be the best ever.  If you're centrist or right-wing, they're the worst place you can possibly be.

This was the worst class and professor I have ever had. She does not teach criminal LAW, she teaches criminology. The grading is way out of proportion as you are expected to write 60+ page journals for this class every two months alongside all your other law courses.No academic freedom in her classroom-forget about having your own opinion.
Professor Backhouse is the best thing that ever happened to this law school. She is truly a visionary and was the whole reason I picked my criminal law course.
